nodes.bodyText: Remove extra "Component" from class name and file name.
enableTracing should be based on whether this is development or not.
empty path usually goes at the end of the routes list.
Better to provide in the ManageAccountModule
Thanks,Updated in the latest commit and I have changed in other Services also
I don't think this needs a route prefix. Having everything nested under user doesn't add any value, and lets us use user in the "manage user" module

I have changed the path to 'admin' and I need SiteCoordinatorModule as a parent module for all nested modules to write common header in SiteCoordinatorComponent and SiteCoordinatorModule will behave as role based module so that in future if new role come we can create new module

Let's not overdesign this for something that might or might not happen. I can be convinced to use a prefix here, but then it has to reflect the specific purpose, so 'coordinator', or rename the site-coordinator module to Admin.
path: 'account/setup'? Do we have other account routes?

I have imported set-up-account in app.module.ts and provided routing for it in app.routing.ts to as set up account will be not be called AuthGuard
I will be making AUthGuard PR once Login will be implemented
I don't understand. If this is being replaced than remove it from this PR
This will not be replaced in the future PR.
Why add another route? If this module only does one thing than just keep the empty path.
The REST convention is to use plurals for collections. As I said, it should be sites not site.

This is a list of participants for a single app. So should this still be called as apps?
Same question for sites and studies.

Can you please explain this comment.
I have given path: ':partcipantId' as I want Id, so I'm mentioning it as  :partcipantId
These seem like Participant routes, not Site routes
Updated in the latest commit and I have changed for remaining components also

This is a list of participants for a single app. So should this still be called as participant-apps or app-participant-list or participant-app?
Same question for sites and studies.
This is a list of participants for a single site. So should this still be called as participant-sites or site-participant-list or participant-site?
This whole app is for managing things. Just call it the UserModule.
